---
title: Walnut-Crusted Salmon with Garlicky Zucchini, Scallion Rice & Creamy Lemon Sauce
description: What’s better than tender, flaky fish with a crunchy topping? How about salmon fillets coated with a tangy, lemon cream sauce, then crusted in a mixture of toasted walnuts, panko, and fresh herbs?! The topping toasts up nice and crisp in the oven as the fish cooks to juicy perfection. Keeping it light, we’re also serving up garlicky roasted zucchini over a fluffy sea of scallion rice, all drizzled with that perky cream sauce. Weeknight luxury is just 30 minutes away!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/walnut-crusted-salmon-29a41755.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/walnut-crusted-salmon-63694ccadae40b54e20bbcb1-cec637da.pdf
course: main course
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/walnut-crusted-salmon-63694ccadae40b54e20bbcb1
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 800 kcal
  fat: 47 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 61 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 290 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a small #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @jasmine rice{½%cup}, ¾ cup water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook, covered, until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, finely chop @walnuts{½%oz} or crush in their bag with a heavy-bottomed pan or #rolling pin{}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Peels and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove} or grate garlic.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, walnuts, and half the @dried oregano{1%tsp}. Toast, stirring, until golden and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer walnut mixture to a small #bowl{}. Season with ¼ tsp @salt{} and @pepper{}. Wipe out pan.

In a second small bowl, combine @yogurt{2%tbsp}, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, half the lemon zest, and a squeeze of lemon juice.

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Pat @salmon{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place, skin sides down, on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Top each piece of salmon with 1 tsp sauce; spread to coat evenly. Mound tops with walnut mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Roast on top rack until salmon is opaque and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

While salmon roasts, heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for walnuts over medium-high heat. Add zucchini; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add garlic, remaining oregano, a big pinch of @salt{}, and pepper. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in half the scallion greens, remaining lemon zest, and a drizzle of @olive oil{4%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide salmon, zucchini, and rice between plates. Drizzle sauce over salmon and sprinkle with remaining scallion greens. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.